{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851421452,"sessionID":"ses_28704e4cdffeDsBqzmqKixki53","part":{"id":"prt_d78fe34a3001z5battELoaxzfn","messageID":"msg_d78fcb925001y5Nju2hby9jJdD","sessionID":"ses_28704e4cdffeDsBqzmqKixki53","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1819da2b93fa481f8c377316","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Atomic Tasks\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Session Data Structures\n18: \n19: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/session/types.go`\n20:   - Define `Session` struct with fields: `ID`, `Namespace`, `Kind`, `BackendName`, `BackendURL`, `UserID`, `CreatedAt`, `LastActivityAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `State`, `Metadata`, `mu`\n21:   - Define `SessionState` type with consts: `SessionStateActive`, `SessionStateIdle`, `SessionStateExpired`, `SessionStateTerminated`\n22:   - Define `SessionConfig` struct with all configuration fields\n23:   - Define `RedisSessionConfig` struct\n24:   - Add `GenerateSessionID()` helper function\n25: \n26: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/session/config.go`\n27:   - Implement `DefaultSessionConfig()` function\n28:   - Implement config validation method `Validate()`\n29:   - Implement environment variable loading\n30: \n31: ### Phase 2: Session Store Interface\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/session/store.go`\n34:   - Define `SessionStore` interface with methods: `Get()`, `Set()`, `Delete()`, `List()`, `ListByUser()`, `Close()`\n35:   - Define error types: `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Create `pkg/router/session/memory_store.go`\n38:   - Implement `MemoryStore` struct with `sync.Map` and `sync.RWMutex`\n39:   - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n40:   - Implement thread-safe concurrent access\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Create `pkg/router/session/redis_store.go`\n43:   - Implement `RedisStore` struct with redis client and config\n44:   - Implement `NewRedisStore()` constructor\n45:   - Implement all `SessionStore` interface methods\n46:   - Implement Redis key schema per design spec\n47:   - Implement connection pool configuration\n48: \n49: ### Phase 3: Session Manager\n50: \n51: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/session/manager.go`\n52:   - Define `SessionManager` struct with fields: `config`, `store`, `metrics`, `stopCh`, `wg`, `mu`\n53:   - Define `SessionMetrics` struct with Prometheus metrics\n54: \n55: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewSessionManager()` constructor\n56:   - Takes config and store\n57:   - Creates metrics\n58:   - Returns initialized *SessionManager\n59: \n60: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `SessionManager.CreateSession()` method\n61:   - Creates new session with provided parameters\n62:   - Generates session ID\n63:   - Stores session in store\n64:   - Records metrics\n65:   - Returns *Session or error\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `SessionManager.GetSession()` method\n68:   - Retrieves session from store by ID\n69:   - Checks expiration\n70:   - Updates last activity timestamp\n71:   - Returns *Session or error\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `SessionManager.UpdateSession()` method\n74:   - Updates session metadata\n75:   - Stores updated session\n76: \n77: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `SessionManager.DeleteSession()` method\n78:   - Terminates session\n79:   - Removes from store\n80:   - Records metrics\n81: \n82: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement `SessionManager.ListSessions()` method\n83:   - Lists sessions matching filters\n84:   - Supports namespace, kind, userID filters\n85: \n86: - [ ] **TASK-027**: Implement `SessionManager.CleanupExpiredSessions()` method\n87:   - Scans for expired sessions\n88:   - Removes expired sessions\n89:   - Returns count of cleaned sessions\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-028**: Implement `SessionManager.Start()` method\n92:   - Starts background cleanup loop\n93:   - Runs initial cleanup\n94: \n95: - [ ] **TASK-029**: Implement `SessionManager.Shutdown()` method\n96:   - Stops cleanup loop\n97:   - Waits for background tasks\n98:   - Persists in-memory sessions (if using memory store)\n99:   - Closes store connection\n100: \n101: ### Phase 4: Session Middleware\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/middleware/session_middleware.go`\n104:   - Define `SessionMiddleware` struct with manager and config\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.ExtractSession()` method\n107:   - Extracts session token from cookie\n108:   - Falls back to header if cookie not present\n109:   - Returns session ID or error\n110: \n111: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.AttachSession()` method\n112:   - Sets session cookie on response\n113:   - Configures cookie properties (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)\n114: \n115: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `SessionMiddleware.WithSession()` method\n116:   - Wraps HTTP handler with session context\n117:   - Validates session token\n118:   - Attaches session to request context\n119: \n120: ### Phase 5: Session Integration with Router\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/session_resolver.go`\n123:   - Implement `ResolveWithSession()` method\n124:   - Check session affinity\n125:   - Reassign backend if unhealthy\n126:   - Update session last activity\n127: \n128: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement session affinity algorithm\n129:   - Priority 1: Session's current backend (if healthy)\n130:   - Priority 2: Least loaded healthy backend\n131: \n132: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Update `pkg/router/handler.go`\n133:   - Integrate session middleware\n134:   - Pass session to resolver\n135: \n136: ### Phase 6: Session Management Endpoints\n137: \n138: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Create `pkg/router/session_handler.go`\n139:   - Define `SessionHandler` struct\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement session management HTTP handlers\n142:   - `ListSessionsHandler()` - GET /sessions\n143:   - `GetSessionHandler()` - GET /sessions/{id}\n144:   - `CreateSessionHandler()` - POST /sessions\n145:   - `DeleteSessionHandler()` - DELETE /sessions/{id}\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement error response format\n148:   - Define `SessionErrorResponse` struct\n149:   - Define error codes constants\n150: \n151: ### Phase 7: Error Handling\n152: \n153: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `pkg/router/session_errors.go`\n154:   - Define session error types:\n155:     - `ErrSessionNotFound`, `ErrSessionExpired`, `ErrSessionTerminated`\n156:     - `ErrSessionCreateFailed`, `ErrSessionStoreError`\n157:     - `ErrBackendUnavailable`, `ErrAffinityBroken`\n158:     - `ErrInvalidSessionConfig`, `ErrRedisConnectionFailed`\n159:   - Define error codes constants\n160: \n161: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement fallback strategy\n162:   - Define `FallbackStrategy` type\n163:   - Implement graceful degradation logic\n164: \n165: ### Phase 8: Testing (TDD)\n166: \n167: #### Unit Tests - Session Types\n168: \n169: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestSession_IsExpired` in `pkg/router/session/session_test.go`\n170:   - Given: Session with ExpiresAt in the past\n171:   - When: IsExpired() called\n172:   - Then: Returns true\n173: \n174: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestSession_IsIdle`\n175:   - Given: Session with LastActivityAt exceeding idle timeout\n176:   - When: IsIdle() called\n177:   - Then: Returns true\n178: \n179: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestSession_UpdateActivity`\n180:   - Given: Active session\n181:   - When: UpdateActivity() called\n182:   - Then: LastActivityAt updated to now\n183: \n184: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestSession_ThreadSafety`\n185:   - Given: Session accessed from multiple goroutines\n186:   - When: Concurrent reads and writes\n187:   - Then: No data race\n188: \n189: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestGenerateSessionID`\n190:   - Given: Multiple calls to GenerateSessionID()\n191:   - When: IDs generated\n192:   - Then: All IDs are unique, follow format `sess_<timestamp>_<random>`\n193: \n194: #### Unit Tests - Memory Store\n195: \n196: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestMemoryStore_GetSet` in `pkg/router/session/memory_store_test.go`\n197:   - Given: Memory store\n198:   - When: Set() then Get()\n199:   - Then: Returns stored session\n200: \n201: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestMemoryStore_Delete`\n202:   - Given: Session in store\n203:   - When: Delete() called\n204:   - Then: Get() returns ErrSessionNotFound\n205: \n206: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestMemoryStore_List`\n207:   - Given: Multiple sessions with different namespaces/kinds\n208:   - When: List() with filters\n209:   - Then: Returns matching sessions\n210: \n211: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestMemoryStore_ListByUser`\n212:   - Given: Sessions for multiple users\n213:   - When: ListByUser() called\n214:   - Then: Returns sessions for specified user\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestMemoryStore_ConcurrentAccess`\n217:   - Given: Memory store\n218:   - When: Concurrent Get/Set/Delete from multiple goroutines\n219:   - Then: No data race, all operations succeed\n220: \n221: #### Unit Tests - Redis Store\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestRedisStore_GetSet` in `pkg/router/session/redis_store_test.go`\n224:   - Given: Redis store with test Redis server\n225:   - When: Set() then Get()\n226:   - Then: Returns stored session\n227: \n228: - [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestRedisStore_Delete`\n229:   - Given: Session in Redis\n230:   - When: Delete() called\n231:   - Then: Session removed\n232: \n233: - [ ] **TEST-022**: `TestRedisStore_List`\n234:   - Given: Multiple sessions in Redis\n235:   - When: List() with filters\n23