TP server\n41: \n42: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Router.Shutdown()` method\n43:   - Stop accepting new connections\n44:   - Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n45:   - Shutdown informers\n46:   - Release resources\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Router.ServeHTTP()` method\n49:   - Delegate to handler\n50: \n51: ### Phase 3: Route Resolver\n52: \n53: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/resolver.go`\n54:   - Implement `Resolve()` method to lookup routes from sync.Map\n55:   - Implement `parsePath()` to extract namespace, resourceType, name from URL path\n56: \n57: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement informer event handlers\n58:   - `onAgentRuntimeAdd()` - add route on CR creation\n59:   - `onAgentRuntimeUpdate()` - update route on CR update\n60:   - `onAgentRuntimeDelete()` - remove route on CR deletion\n61:   - `onCodeInterpreterAdd/Update/Delete()` - same for CodeInterpreter\n62: \n63: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handler\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/handler.go`\n66:   - Define `Handler` struct\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `Handler.ProxyRequest()` method\n69:   - Build backend URL from RouteEntry\n70:   - Clone request with new context\n71:   - Add forwarding headers (X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-Host, X-Forwarded-Proto)\n72:   - Execute request via httpClient.Do()\n73:   - Copy response headers and body\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Handler.writeErrorResponse()` method\n76:   - Write JSON error response with appropriate status code\n77: \n78: ### Phase 5: Health Check Manager\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/health.go`\n81:   - Define `HealthChecker` struct\n82: \n83: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `HealthChecker.Start()` method\n84:   - Periodic health check loop\n85:   - Check backend health at configured interval\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `HealthChecker.CheckHealth()` method\n88:   - HTTP GET to backend health endpoint\n89:   - Update HealthStatus based on response\n90:   - Apply health check failure policy (3 failures → mark unhealthy)\n91: \n92: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `HealthChecker.MarkUnhealthy()` and `HealthChecker.MarkHealthy()` methods\n93: \n94: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `/healthz` HTTP handler\n95:   - Check informer sync status\n96:   - Return HTTP 200/503 based on health\n97: \n98: ### Phase 6: Error Handling\n99: \n100: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Define error types in `pkg/router/errors.go`\n101:   - `ErrRouteNotFound`, `ErrNoHealthyBackends`, `ErrInvalidResourceType`, `ErrMalformedPath`\n102:   - `ErrBackendConnection`, `ErrBackendTimeout`, `ErrBackendUnavailable`\n103: \n104: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement error-to-HTTP-status mapping\n105: \n106: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (TDD)\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `pkg/router/router_test.go`\n109:   - `TestRouter_Start`\n110:   - `TestRouter_Shutdown`\n111:   - `TestRouter_routeKey`\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `pkg/router/resolver_test.go`\n114:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success`\n115:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound`\n116:   - `TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy`\n117:   - `TestResolver_ParsePath`\n118: \n119: - [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `pkg/router/health_test.go`\n120:   - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success`\n121:   - `TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure`\n122:   - `TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy`\n123:   - `TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `pkg/router/handler_test.go`\n126:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success`\n127:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError`\n128:   - `TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout`\n129:   - `TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `pkg/router/config_test.go`\n132:   - `TestDefaultRouterConfig`\n133:   - `TestRouterConfig_Validate`\n134: \n135: ### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `pkg/router/router_integration_test.go`\n138:   - Test CRD creation triggers route addition\n139:   - Test CRD deletion triggers route removal\n140:   - End-to-end request routing\n141:   - Health check removes unhealthy backend\n142:   - Concurrent request handling\n143: \n144: ### Phase 9: Documentation\n145: \n146: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/doc.go`\n147: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n148: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Verify `pkg/router/design.md` is complete\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Acceptance Criteria\n153: \n154: - [ ] Router initializes with Kubernetes clientset and informers\n155: - [ ] HTTP requests are routed to correct backend based on CRD resources\n156: - [ ] Informer watches update routes on CRD create/update/delete\n157: - [ ] Namespace-based routing works correctly\n158: - [ ] `/healthz` endpoint returns accurate health status\n159: - [ ] Connection pooling configured with timeouts\n160: - [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n161: - [ ] Graceful shutdown waits for in-flight requests\n162: - [ ] All unit tests pass with ≥85% coverage\n163: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real CRDs\n164: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Dependencies\n169: \n170: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n171: |------------|--------|-------|\n172: | `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Kubernetes API client |\n173: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | External | Resource types |\n174: | `net/http/httputil` | Go stdlib | Reverse proxy |\n175: | `go.uber.org/zap` | External | Structured logging |\n176: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | External | Metrics (optional) |\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Implementation Order\n181: \n182: ```\n183: TASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013\n184:                               ↓\n185: TASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-030 → TASK-031 → TASK-032\n186:                               ↓\n187: TASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → TASK-044\n188:                               ↓\n189: TASK-050 → TASK-051\n190:                   