thorized\n  Line 79:   Given a JWT token with aud claim not matching configuration\n  Line 82:   And the router SHALL return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n  Line 88: ### R-2: JWT Token Issuance\n  Line 90: **Given** a token request endpoint `/api/v1/auth/token`  \n  Line 93: - Verify credentials against Kubernetes service account or configured auth source\n  Line 94: - Use client-go to validate service account existence if using K8s auth\n  Line 95: - Generate a JWT token with appropriate claims\n  Line 105:   And a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/token\" with service account token\n  Line 107:   Then a JWT token SHALL be generated\n  Line 116:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/token\" is received\n  Line 118:   And the router SHALL return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n  Line 128:   Given a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/token\" without credentials\n  Line 135:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/token\" is received\n  Line 144: **Given** a valid JWT token with refresh capability  \n  Line 145: **When** a refresh request is received at `/api/v1/auth/refresh`  \n  Line 156:   Given a valid JWT token that is not expired\n  Line 157:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/refresh\" is received with the token\n  Line 164:   Given an expired JWT token\n  Line 165:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/refresh\" is received\n  Line 167:   And the router SHALL return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n  Line 171:   Given refresh is disabled in JWT configuration\n  Line 172:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/refresh\" is received\n  Line 179: ### R-4: JWT Configuration\n  Line 182: **When** JWT configuration is loaded  \n  Line 194: Scenario: Load JWT config from environment variables\n  Line 195:   Given environment variables JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRY, JWT_ISSUER are set\n  Line 198:   And the values SHALL be applied to JWT validation\n  Line 200: Scenario: JWT config missing secret key\n  Line 201:   Given JWT_SECRET environment variable is not set\n  Line 204:   And an error SHALL be returned indicating \"missing JWT secret\"\n  Line 206: Scenario: JWT config with invalid expiry duration\n  Line 207:   Given JWT_EXPIRY is set to a non-duration string\n  Line 212: Scenario: JWT config from file\n  Line 213:   Given a JWT config file at /etc/agentcube/jwt-config.yaml\n  Line 224: **When** JWT middleware is configured  \n  Line 226: - Protect specified routes with JWT validation\n  Line 236:   Given JWT middleware is registered for \"/api/v1/agents/*\"\n  Line 240:   And return HTTP 401 Unauthorized due to missing token\n  Line 242: Scenario: Public path bypasses authentication\n  Line 249:   Given a valid JWT token with user_id=\"agent-1\" and role=\"admin\"\n  Line 258:   And public routes SHALL allow unauthenticated access\n  Line 265: **Given** authentication method is set to \"serviceaccount\"  \n  Line 319:   Given a valid JWT token exists\n  Line 320:   When a POST request to \"/api/v1/auth/revoke\" is received with the token\n  Line 329:   And return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n  Line 343: **Given** the router handles authentication events  \n  Line 344: **When** authentication operations occur  \n  Line 348: - Log authentication failures with reason\n  Line 355: Scenario: Log successful authentication\n  Line 357:   When authentication succeeds\n  Line 362: Scenario: Log authentication failure\n  Line 364:   When authentication fails\n  Line 383: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | External | JWT parsing and signing |\n  Line 392: ### JWTConfig\n  Line 395: type JWTConfig struct {\n  Line 401:     AuthMethod     string        `json:\"auth_method\" yaml:\"auth_method\"` // serviceaccount|config|none\n  Line 409:     jwt.RegisteredClaims\n  Line 422:     Token          string `json:\"token,omitempty\"` // For token-based auth\n  Line 440: ### JWTAuthenticator\n  Line 443: type JWTAuthenticator interface {\n  Line 454: func JWTMiddleware(auth JWTAuthenticator, skipPaths ...string) gin.HandlerFunc\n  Line 463: | `pkg/router/auth/jwt.go` | Create 