{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851657989,"sessionID":"ses_28704e4cdffeDsBqzmqKixki53","part":{"id":"prt_d79004896001HSdNs2DNVkmZvC","messageID":"msg_d79003b12001xTLe7p1ysSTV0X","sessionID":"ses_28704e4cdffeDsBqzmqKixki53","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_6dd094ace1f543cf8671101c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","content":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design Stage | ST-3 (Completed) |\n\n---\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: JWT Types and Claims\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `pkg/router/auth/types.go`\n  - Define `TokenClaims` struct with fields: `jwt.RegisteredClaims`, `UserID`, `Role`, `TenantID`\n  - Define `TokenRequest` struct with fields: `ServiceAccount`, `Namespace`, `Token`\n  - Define `TokenResponse` struct with fields: `Token`, `ExpiresAt`, `TokenType`\n  - Define `TokenBlacklistEntry` struct for revocation\n  - Add constants for token types, claim keys\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Create `pkg/router/auth/config.go`\n  - Define `JWTConfig` struct with fields: `SecretKey`, `Expiration`, `Issuer`, `Audience`, `RefreshEnabled`, `AuthMethod`\n  - Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` function\n  - Implement config validation method `Validate()`\n  - Define auth method constants: `AuthMethodServiceAccount`, `AuthMethodConfig`, `AuthMethodNone`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Create `pkg/router/auth/config_loader.go`\n  - Implement `LoadJWTConfigFromEnv()` function\n  - Implement `LoadJWTConfigFromFile()` function\n  - Implement environment variable loading (JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRY, JWT_ISSUER, JWT_AUDIENCE, JWT_REFRESH_ENABLED, JWT_AUTH_METHOD)\n  - Implement file-based config loading from YAML\n  - Implement config merging (file → env override)\n  - Add validation and error handling\n\n### Phase 2: JWT Authenticator Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Create `pkg/router/auth/jwt.go`\n  - Define `JWTAuthenticator` interface with methods: `Validate()`, `Issue()`, `Refresh()`, `Revoke()`\n  - Define `jwtAuthenticator` struct with fields: `config`, `signingKey`, `blacklist`, `k8sClient`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewJWTAuthenticator()` constructor\n  - Takes `*JWTConfig` and optional kubernetes clientset\n  - Initializes signing key from config\n  - Creates token blacklist\n  - Returns `JWTAuthenticator` or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `JWTAuthenticator.Issue()` method\n  - Create `TokenClaims` with provided user info\n  - Set `iat`, `exp`, `nbf` claims\n  - Set `iss`, `aud` claims from config\n  - Generate unique `jti` claim\n  - Sign token with configured secret key\n  - Return signed JWT token string\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `JWTAuthenticator.Validate()` method\n  - Parse JWT token string\n  - Verify signature using secret key\n  - Validate `exp` claim (not expired)\n  - Validate `nbf` claim (not before)\n  - Validate `iss` claim matches config\n  - Validate `aud` claim matches config\n  - Check token not in blacklist\n  - Return `*TokenClaims` or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `JWTAuthenticator.Refresh()` method\n  - Validate existing token\n  - Check if refresh is enabled in config\n  - Extract original claims\n  - Create new token with updated `exp`, `iat`, `jti`\n  - Preserve `user_id`, `role`, `tenant_id`\n  - Return new token string\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `JWTAuthenticator.Revoke()` method\n  - Parse token to extract `jti`\n  - Add `jti` to blacklist\n  - Set blacklist entry expiration\n  - Return error if fails\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement service account credential verification\n  - Use `CoreV1().ServiceAccounts(namespace).Get()` to verify existence\n  - Cache service account lookups\n  - Support token-based SA verification\n  - Return error if SA not found or verification fails\n\n### Phase 3: Token Blacklist Management\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Create `pkg/router/blacklist/blacklist.go`\n  - Define `TokenBlacklist` interface with methods: `Add()`, `Contains()`, `Remove()`, `Cleanup()`\n  - Define `MemoryBlacklist` struct with `sync.Map` and `sync.RWMutex`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewMemoryBlacklist()` constructor\n  - Initializes in-memory blacklist\n  - Returns `*MemoryBlacklist`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `MemoryBlacklist.Add()` method\n  - Add token JTI to blacklist\n  - Set expiration time\n  - Thread-safe operation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `MemoryBlacklist.Contains()` method\n  - Check if JTI exists in blacklist\n  - Check if entry has expired\n  - Return boolean\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `MemoryBlacklist.Remove()` method\n  - Remove JTI from blacklist\n  - Thread-safe operation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `MemoryBlacklist.Cleanup()` method\n  - Scan for expired entries\n  - Remove expired entries\n  - Return count of cleaned entries\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Create Redis-backed blacklist (optional)\n  - Implement `RedisBlacklist` struct\n  - Use Redis SET with TTL for automatic expiration\n  - Implement all interface methods\n\n### Phase 4: HTTP Handlers\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Create `pkg/router/handlers/token.go`\n  - Define `TokenHandler` struct with `authenticator` and `config`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `TokenHandler.IssueToken()` handler\n  - POST `/api/v1/auth/token`\n  - Parse request body to `TokenRequest`\n  - Validate credentials\n  - Call `authenticator.Issue()`\n  - Return `TokenResponse` with HTTP 200\n  - Handle errors: 400 (missing creds), 401 (invalid creds), 503 (disabled)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `TokenHandler.RefreshToken()` handler\n  - POST `/api/v1/auth/refresh`\n  - Extract token from Authorization header\n  - Call `authenticator.Refresh()`\n  - Return `TokenResponse` with HTTP 200\n  - Handle errors: 401 (expired/invalid), 503 (refresh disabled)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Create `pkg/router/handlers/revoke.go`\n  - Define `RevokeHandler` struct\n\n- [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `RevokeHandler.RevokeToken()` handler\n  - POST `/api/v1/auth/revoke`\n  - Extract token from Authorization header\n  - Call `authenticator.Revoke()`\n  - Return success response with HTTP 200\n  - Handle errors: 400 (invalid token), 503 (revocation disabled)\n\n### Phase 5: Authentication Middleware\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Create `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go`\n  - Define `AuthMiddleware` struct with `authenticator`, `skipPaths`, `protectedPrefixes`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewAuthMiddleware()` constructor\n  - Takes `JWTAuthenticator` and optional skip paths\n  - Returns `*AuthMiddleware`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `AuthMiddleware.ExtractToken()` method\n  - Extract token from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n  - Validate header format\n  - Return token string or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `AuthMiddleware.WithAuth()` method\n  - Wrap HTTP handler with JWT validation\n  - Skip validation for paths in skip list\n  - Extract and validate token\n  - Attach claims to request context\n  - Return 401 on validation failure\n  - Call next handler on success\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `AuthMiddleware.AttachClaimsToContext()` method\n  - Store `*TokenClaims` in request context\n  - Use context key type for type safety\n\n- [ ] **TASK-045**: Create `pkg/router/middleware/context.go`\n  - Define context key type\n  - Implement `GetClaimsFromContext()` helper\n  - Implement `GetUserIDFromContext()` helper\n  - Implement `GetRoleFromContext()` helper\n\n### Phase 6: Router Integration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Update `pkg/router/router.go`\n  - Add `authMiddleware` field to `Router` struct\n  - Add `jwtAuthenticator` field to `Router` struct\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement router middleware registration\n  - Register auth middleware in `NewRouter()`\n  - Apply middleware to protected routes\n  - Configure skip paths for health checks and token endpoints\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Update route registration\n  - Mark routes as protected or public\n  - Apply auth middleware selectively\n  - Ensure `/healthz`, `/api/v1/auth/*` are public\n\n### Phase 7: Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Create `pkg/router/auth/k8s_client.go`\n  - Implement `NewKubernetesClientset()` function\n  - Use `clientset.NewForConfig()` to create clientset\n  - Support in-cluster and out-of-cluster config\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `VerifyServiceAccount()` function\n  - Call `CoreV1().ServiceAccounts(namespace).Get()`\n  - Handle NotFound error\n  - Cache results to reduce API calls\n  - Return error if verification fails\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement service account informer (optional)\n  - Use `SharedInformerFactory` for caching\n  - Implement event handlers for SA changes\n  - Reduce repeated API calls\n\n### Phase 8: Logging and Audit\n\n- [ ] **TASK-070**: Create `pkg/router/auth/audit.go`\n  - Define audit log structure\n  - Implement `LogAuthSuccess()` function\n  - Implement `LogAuthFailure()` function\n  - Implement `LogTokenIssuance()` function\n  - Implement `LogTokenRevocation()` function\n\n- [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement structured logging\n  - Use zap or logrus for structured logging\n  - Include request ID, user ID, method, path, duration\n  - NEVER log token values\n  - Log failure reasons\n\n### Phase 9: Error Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-080**: Create `pkg/router/auth/errors.go`\n  - Define error types:\n    - `ErrMissingToken`, `ErrInvalidToken`, `ErrExpiredToken`\n    - `ErrInvalidSignature`, `ErrInvalidIssuer`, `ErrInvalidAudience`\n    - `ErrTokenBlacklisted`, `ErrRefreshDisabled`\n    - `ErrMissingCredentials`, `ErrInvalidCredentials`\n    - `ErrServiceAccountNotFound`, `ErrKubernetesClientFailed`\n  - Define error codes constants for HTTP responses\n  - Implement error-to-HTTP-status mapping\n\n### Phase 10: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - JWT Types and Config\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestTokenClaims_MarshalJSON` in `pkg/router/auth/types_test.go`\n  - Given: TokenClaims with user_id, role, tenant_id\n  - When: Marshaled to JSON\n  - Then: JSON contains all claims including registered claims\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestJWTConfig_Validate` in `pkg/router/auth/config_test.go`\n  - Given: Various config combinations\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns error for missing secret, invalid expiry\n  - And: Returns nil for valid config\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestLoadJWTConfigFromEnv`\n  - Given: Environment variables JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRY set\n  - When: LoadJWTConfigFromEnv() called\n  - Then: Config loaded with correct values\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestLoadJWTConfigFromFile`\n  - Given: YAML config file exists\n  - When: LoadJWTConfigFromFile() called\n  - Then: Config loaded from file\n\n#### Unit Tests - JWT Authenticator\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Issue` in `pkg/router/auth/jwt_test.go`\n  - Given: Configured JWTAuthenticator\n  - When: Issue() called with valid claims\n  - Then: Returns signed JWT token\n  - And: Token contains correct claims\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_Success`\n  - Given: Valid JWT token\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns TokenClaims\n  - And: No error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_ExpiredToken`\n  - Given: Expired JWT token\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrExpiredToken\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_InvalidSignature`\n  - Given: Token signed with different key\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrInvalidSignature\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_InvalidIssuer`\n  - Given: Token with wrong issuer claim\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrInvalidIssuer\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_InvalidAudience`\n  - Given: Token with wrong audience claim\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrInvalidAudience\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Validate_Blacklisted`\n  - Given: Token JTI in blacklist\n  - When: Validate() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrTokenBlacklisted\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Refresh`\n  - Given: Valid non-expired token\n  - When: Refresh() called\n  - Then: Returns new token with same claims\n  - And: New token has updated exp, iat, jti\n\n- [ ] **TEST-018**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Refresh_ExpiredToken`\n  - Given: Expired token\n  - When: Refresh() called\n  - Then: Returns error\n  - And: No new token issued\n\n- [ ] **TEST-019**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Refresh_Disabled`\n  - Given: Refresh disabled in config\n  - When: Refresh() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrRefreshDisabled\n  - And: HTTP 503 returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_Revoke`\n  - Given: Valid token\n  - When: Revoke() called\n  - Then: Token JTI added to blacklist\n  - And: Subsequent Validate() fails\n\n#### Unit Tests - Token Blacklist\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestMemoryBlacklist_Add_Contains` in `pkg/router/blacklist/blacklist_test.go`\n  - Given: Empty blacklist\n  - When: Add() called, then Contains() called\n  - Then: Contains() returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestMemoryBlacklist_Remove`\n  - Given: JTI in blacklist\n  - When: Remove() called\n  - Then: Contains() returns false\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestMemoryBlacklist_Cleanup`\n  - Given: Mix of expired and active entries\n  - When: Cleanup() called\n  - Then: Only expired entries removed\n  - And: Returns count of cleaned entries\n\n- [ ] **TEST-033**: `TestMemoryBlacklist_ConcurrentAccess`\n  - Given: Blacklist\n  - When: Concurrent Add/Contains/Remove from multiple goroutines\n  - Then: No data race, all operations succeed\n\n#### Unit Tests - HTTP Handlers\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: `TestTokenHandler_IssueToken_Success` in `pkg/router/handlers/token_test.go`\n  - Given: Valid service account credentials\n  - When: POST /api/v1/auth/token\n  - Then: HTTP 200 returned\n  - And: Response contains token\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: `TestTokenHandler_IssueToken_MissingCredentials`\n  - Given: No credentials in request\n  - When: POST /api/v1/auth/token\n  - Then: HTTP 400 returned\n  - And: Error indicates missing credentials\n\n- [ ] **TEST-042**: `TestTokenHandler_IssueToken_InvalidCredentials`\n  - Given: Non-existent service account\n  - When: POST /api/v1/auth/token\n  - Then: HTTP 401 returned\n  - And: No token issued\n\n- [ ] **TEST-043**: `TestTokenHandler_RefreshToken_Success`\n  - Given: Valid non-expired token\n  - When: POST /api/v1/auth/refresh\n  - Then: HTTP 200 returned\n  - And: New token in response\n\n- [ ] **TEST-044**: `TestRevokeHandler_RevokeToken`\n  - Given: Valid token\n  - When: POST /api/v1/auth/revoke\n  - Then: HTTP 200 returned\n  - And: Token added to blacklist\n\n#### Unit Tests - Auth Middleware\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: `TestAuthMiddleware_WithAuth_ValidToken` in `pkg/router/middleware/auth_test.go`\n  - Given: Request with valid JWT token\n  - When: WithAuth() middleware processes request\n  - Then: Request proceeds to handler\n  - And: Claims attached to context\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: `TestAuthMiddleware_WithAuth_MissingToken`\n  - Given: Request without token\n  - When: WithAuth() middleware processes request\n  - Then: HTTP 401 returned\n  - And: Handler not called\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: `TestAuthMiddleware_WithAuth_InvalidToken`\n  - Given: Request with invalid token\n  - When: WithAuth() middleware processes request\n  - Then: HTTP 401 returned\n  - And: Error response indicates reason\n\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: `TestAuthMiddleware_WithAuth_SkipPath`\n  - Given: Request to /healthz (skip path)\n  - When: WithAuth() middleware processes request\n  - Then: Validation skipped\n  - And: Request proceeds to handler\n\n- [ ] **TEST-054**: `TestAuthMiddleware_ExtractToken`\n  - Given: Request with \"Authorization: Bearer <token>\" header\n  - When: ExtractToken() called\n  - Then: Returns token string\n  - And: No error\n\n#### Unit Tests - Kubernetes Client\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: `TestVerifyServiceAccount_Exists` in `pkg/router/auth/k8s_client_test.go`\n  - Given: ServiceAccount exists in fake clientset\n  - When: VerifyServiceAccount() called\n  - Then: Returns nil\n  - And: SA verified as existing\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: `TestVerifyServiceAccount_NotFound`\n  - Given: ServiceAccount does not exist\n  - When: VerifyServiceAccount() called\n  - Then: Returns ErrServiceAccountNotFound\n  - And: HTTP 401 returned\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-070**: `TestJWTAuthenticator_EndToEnd` in `pkg/router/auth/integration_test.go`\n  - Use real JWT signing and validation\n  - Issue token, validate, refresh, revoke\n  - Verify full lifecycle works\n\n- [ ] **TEST-071**: `TestAuthMiddleware_Integration`\n  - Setup test HTTP server with middleware\n  - Send requests with various tokens\n  - Verify middleware behavior\n\n- [ ] **TEST-072**: `TestTokenHandler_Integration`\n  - Setup test HTTP server\n  - Test token issuance with fake clientset\n  - Test refresh and revocation\n\n- [ ] **TEST-073**: `TestBlacklist_RedisBackend` (if Redis enabled)\n  - Use testcontainers or miniredis\n  - Verify blacklist persists in Redis\n  - Verify TTL-based expiration\n\n#### Performance Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-080**: `BenchmarkJWTAuthenticator_Issue` in `pkg/router/auth/bench_test.go`\n  - Benchmark token issuance latency\n\n- [ ] **TEST-081**: `BenchmarkJWTAuthenticator_Validate`\n  - Benchmark token validation latency\n\n- [ ] **TEST-082**: `BenchmarkMemoryBlacklist_Operations`\n  - Benchmark blacklist Add/Contains operations\n\n### Phase 11: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/auth/doc.go`\n  - Package overview\n  - JWT authentication architecture\n  - Configuration options\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n  - Document parameters, return values\n  - Document error conditions\n  - Include examples where applicable\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/blacklist/doc.go`\n  - Blacklist architecture\n  - Memory vs Redis backends\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Add package documentation to `pkg/router/handlers/doc.go`\n  - Handler endpoints\n  - Request/response formats\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Add godoc comments to middleware\n  - Usage examples\n  - Skip path configuration\n\n- [ ] **DOC-006**: Update `pkg/router/README.md`\n  - Add JWT authentication section\n  - Document configuration options\n  - List environment variables\n  - Document token endpoints\n\n- [ ] **DOC-007**: Verify `pkg/router/delta-spec.md` is complete\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT tokens can be signed with configurable algorithms (HS256/HS512)\n- [ ] JWT tokens are validated for signature, expiration, issuer, audience\n- [ ] Token expiration is enforced\n- [ ] Token refresh mechanism works correctly\n- [ ] Token revocation adds to blacklist\n- [ ] Blacklisted tokens are rejected\n- [ ] Authentication middleware integrates with router\n- [ ] Protected routes require valid tokens\n- [ ] Public routes bypass authentication\n- [ ] Claims attached to request context\n- [ ] Service account verification works with client-go\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with ≥85% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with fake clientset\n- [ ] Performance: Token validation overhead < 5ms p99\n- [ ] Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n- [ ] Audit logging implemented (without logging tokens)\n- [ ] Secret key never logged\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n- [ ] Environment variables documented\n- [ ] Security considerations addressed (HTTPS, short expiry, RBAC)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | External | JWT parsing and signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | External | Service account validation |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | External | ServiceAccount type |\n| `pkg/router` (AR-009) | Internal | Router base module |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | External | Redis-backed blacklist (optional) |\n| `go.uber.org/zap` | External | Structured logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n```\nTASK-001 → TASK-002 → TASK-003\n                  ↓\nTASK-010 → TASK-011 → TASK-012 → TASK-013 → TASK-014 → TASK-015 → TASK-016\n                  ↓\nTASK-020 → TASK-021 → TASK-022 → TASK-023 → TASK-024 → TASK-025 → TASK-026\n                  ↓\nTASK-030 → TASK-031 → TASK-032 → TASK-033 → TASK-034\n                  ↓\nTASK-040 → TASK-041 → TASK-042 → TASK-043 → TASK-044 → TASK-045\n                  ↓\nTASK-050 → TASK-051 → TASK-052\n                  ↓\nTASK-060 → TASK-061 → TASK-062\n                  ↓\nTASK-070 → TASK-071\n                  ↓\nTASK-080\n                  ↓\nTEST-001 → ... → TEST-082\n                  ↓\nDOC-001 → ... → DOC-007\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775851657941,"end":1775851657984}}}}
